residents education department of psychiatry stanford university school of medicine stanford school of medicine psychiatry and behavioral sciences search this site only stanford medical sites ways to give find a person alumni lane library ways to give find a person adult psychiatry residency training program residency directors residency training directors chris hayward md mph belinda bandstra md ma & sallie degolia md mph set in a department with a long tradition of innovation and academic excellence stanford's adult psychiatry residency program strives to provide residents with an outstanding and balanced educational experience we offer broad clinical exposure in a diverse array of clinical settings ranging from stanford university medical center and the va health care system to county hospitals and an hmo the program emphasizes biological psychological and sociocultural aspects of psychiatry and provides training in both somatic and psychotherapeutic treatment modalities as every residency program has its own personality ours could be described as flexible and friendly we seek future leaders in psychiatry who wish to pursue a wide range of psychiatric careers including research teaching administration or public sector work we help residents develop their strengths and work with them in every step of their training to help foster their future careers residents develop and pursue their personal and academic objectives with the support and guidance of world class academic and clinical faculty we offer a four year acgme accredited program filled through the national residency matching program nrmp we also have a research track adapted to the scientific interests of the resident the psychiatry department boasts one of the largest research programs within stanford medical center with over 350 research and clinical faculty encompassing a broad range of interests and orientations stanford offers excellent opportunities for all residents to participate in a rich array of research and clinical experiences after the completion of residency there are multiple opportunities for advanced training please feel free to contact us should you have any questions we look forward to hearing from you chris hayward md mph residency training director associate chair of education & training sallie degolia md mph associate residency training director belinda bandstra md ma assistant residency training director you are here stanford medicine school of medicine departments psychiatry education residents navigation for this section psychiatry home education adult psychiatry residency education quality of life application procedure related links grand rounds pgsp stanford psy d consortium about stanford research patient care community divisions programs & centers faculty about us site navigation home education overview adult psychiatry residency grand rounds pgsp stanford psy d consortium c hild psychiatry training program psychosomatic medicine fellowship program about stanford research overview by faculty by topic clinical trials patient care overview inpatient clinics and centers adult out patient clinics adult clinical trials clinics phone directory community overview divisions programs & centers overview faculty department chair academic faculty clinician educators affiliated lecturer senior lecturer adjunct clinical faculty administration stanford medicine resources stanford medicine getting care overview find a physician find a clinical care center stanford hospital & clinics lucile packard children's hospital emergency research overview school of medicine news & resources clinical trials departments institutes & centers faculty profiles education & training overview school of medicine programs admissions continuing medical education alumni lane medical library community overview stanford health library community newsletter volunteering public service & community partnerships renewal & new building projects about us overview news careers ways to g